<span id="freeTextContainer9563862098011690477">So this was definitely a 3-star or maybe a 4-star book in the middle, because I didn’t feel like there was much driving the story forward. But history is history and it’s not always gripping. 😆 Then the Civil War happened, and I couldn’t stop— turning pages or crying. 😆 The backstory on the Lees is powerful— that he would think that of course the Union has to be preserved and then to fight against that for four long years; that he would regret choosing his military education; that MCL would lose</span>
  <span id="freeText9563862098011690477" style="display:none">So this was definitely a 3-star or maybe a 4-star book in the middle, because I didn’t feel like there was much driving the story forward. But history is history and it’s not always gripping. 😆 Then the Civil War happened, and I couldn’t stop— turning pages or crying. 😆 The backstory on the Lees is powerful— that he would think that of course the Union has to be preserved and then to fight against that for four long years; that he would regret choosing his military education; that MCL would lose Arlington, never to return; that Selina would stand up to a Union officer and tell them to stop looting— so many parts in this book really moved me. Will definitely stick with me for a while. Can’t wait to visit Arlington! Highly recommend 👍🏼📖⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️</span>
